# bmad_demo — CODEOWNERS
#
# Routes mandatory review for every PR. The portal teaches governance,
# so the portal practices what it teaches: every path touched by a PR
# auto-routes to one or more code owners who must approve before merge.
# Branch protection on `main` must have "Require review from Code
# Owners" enabled for these rules to enforce; without it, this file is
# documentation only. See CONTRIBUTING.md for the full gate wiring.
#
# Routing model (mix of individual + team handles for clarity in
# stakeholder demos):
#   - @JoshuaEngelbrecht         — current maintainer, single human point
#                                  of contact for repo-wide decisions.
#   - @IAM/lead-engineers        — leads who own infra, governance,
#                                  config, and architectural decisions.
#                                  Required on changes that shape how
#                                  the team works (CI, CODEOWNERS, etc.).
#   - @IAM/engineers             — broader engineering group; reviews
#                                  application code and curriculum.
#   - @IAM/product-team          — product owners; required on planning
#                                  artifacts (PRD, architecture, epics)
#                                  where scope decisions live.
#
# Two-owner rules use AND semantics in GitHub: BOTH owners must approve
# before the gate is satisfied. Use sparingly — every additional owner
# slows review.
#
# Ordering: last matching pattern wins. Catch-all on top, more specific
# rules below override it.

# Catch-all — anything not matched by a more specific rule.
# Maintainer + leads as the safety net for unowned paths.
*                               @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers

# Application code (Next.js + Express handlers + adapters).
# Engineers own day-to-day code; maintainer also routed for v1 oversight.
/src/                           @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/engineers

# Curriculum content (lessons, labs, audience guides, checklists).
# Lead-reviewed because curriculum shapes how teams adopt BMAD.
/training/                      @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers

# Implementation artifacts (per-story specs, retros, sprint status).
# Engineers + maintainer own these — same shape as the code they spec.
/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/   @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/engineers

# Planning artifacts (PRD, architecture, epics, brief, ux-design).
# Product team is mandatory here — scope and product decisions live in
# these files and need a product owner's sign-off.
/_bmad-output/planning-artifacts/         @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers @IAM/product-team

# BMAD framework install (skills, scripts, configs). Changes here are
# rare but high-blast-radius; leads-only.
/_bmad/                         @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers

# Devcontainer / build / runtime infra. Changes here affect every
# trainee's first-run experience — leads-only.
/.devcontainer/                 @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/.github/                       @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/.github/CODEOWNERS             @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/scripts/                       @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers

# Top-level config that shapes the whole app — leads-only.
/next.config.ts                 @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/tsconfig.json                  @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/postcss.config.mjs             @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/eslint.config.mjs              @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/playwright.config.ts           @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/vitest.config.ts               @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/package.json                   @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/package-lock.json              @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers

# Trainee-facing docs (governance docs are leads-only because they
# shape contributor expectations).
/README.md                      @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/CONTRIBUTING.md                @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
/AGENTS.md                      @JoshuaEngelbrecht @IAM/lead-engineers
